NWARDS. PRESSURE WILL REMAIN HIGH IN THE ATLANTIC.
OVERNIGHT MONDAY INTO TUESDAY NE GALES WILL AFFECT SEA
AREA WIGHT AND THE WERN HALF OF SEA AREA FAIR ISLE. STRG
E WINDS WILL AFFECT SEA AREAS FISHER AND FORTIES. BY DAWN
GALES WILL HAVE CEASED IN WIGHT BUT PERSIST THROUGH FAIR
ISLE BEFORE EASING LATER IN THE DAY AS W GALES ONCE AGAIN
DEVELOP IN THE ENGLISH CHANNEL AFFECTING SEA AREAS
